ing overwhelmed and having to.. actually finish the story in this final chapter, i felt this was glossed over so quickly. I get that she already went through a lot of weirdness so not a lot would phase her but learning you're a test-tube baby and getting double the confirmation on how much of a double whammy twat your mom actually is to only go \"oh, okay\"..? The complete lack of emotion near the end (of a ton of characters, not just Zoe) just reaffirms they were rushing through things to get it over with. \n\n- \"Benrime\"\nMultiple mentions of her throughout the game, would've been a small nostalgia nod to returning players. Jakai's sacrifice/betrayal was met with zero payoff, not even a small nod if she's okay in the epilogue for it. I'm simply going to assume she's okay.\n\n- \"Kian & Alayna\"\nRagnar says he always intended for Kian to be gay, i seriously find that hard to believe when he's made various comments about how hot the magical women look in Marcuria and the sexual tension between him and April in previous entries. Ultimately, even with Alayna shoehorned in as a physical gaydar, i don't give a shit about his sexual preference but i do have issues with how poorly it is delivered and how it contradicts established lore. I wonder what compelled them to even add this, i get that you get some brownie-points with the LGBT community for this but really, what did it even add to the narrative? Why didn't blind bob shout he was straight awkwardly? At least we get a boatride with what is probably the single worst delivery of the line \"I AM GAY\" ever. Couldn't we have skipped the boatride and seen some people getting rescued, Benrime perhaps?\nHis sexual preference wasn't the only odd design choice for him. Early on in the game when arriving at the pub, he mentions he doesn't drink at all. later? he remarks that the beer is okay. Even later? He's comparing wines to the ones he's had back home. Which is it?\n\n- \"Saga/Lady Alvane/Deus Ex Machina\"\nIt was grea