t Part?[/b]\nThe plot does get a little bit... convoluted... near the end.  Feels like they were rushing things a bit to wrap up all the loose ends from the first two games.  I'm still pleased with the ending, mind you, it just got a bit twisty, that's all.  Also, remember Lord of the Rings with all the \"epilogues\"?  Same sort of thing going on here.\n\n[b]Will I Like It?[/b]\nIf you enjoyed the previous games in the series, absolutely!\n\n[b]Should I Buy It?[/b]\nObviously, I think so.  But use your enjoyment of the first two games as a guide.  As fantastic as this game is on its own, I doubt it would \"make up for\" the other two, if you didn't enjoy them.\n\nThis has been a 5TYSK review. (#0012)", "timestamp_updated": 1506693537, "written_during_early_access": false, "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "timestamp_created": 1506613572, "votes_down": 0}, {"recommendationid": "35393914", "steam_purchase": true, "votes_up": 1, "weighted_vote_score": "0.502488", "voted_up": true, "language": "english", "author": {"last_played": 1506886151, "steamid": "76561197971289141", "num_games_owned": 139, "num_reviews": 12, "playtime_forever": 2449, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 1415}, "votes_funny": 0, "review": "I got this game on discount and it yielded about 40 hours of gameplay. The story felt weak at the start, but got really interesting by book 3. So if you get it, make sure you give it some time.", "timestamp_updated": 1506886252, "written_during_early_access": false, "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "timestamp_created": 1506886252, "votes_down": 0}, {"recommendationid": "35095737", "steam_purchase": true, "votes_up": 2, "weighted_vote_score": "0.502031", "voted_up": true, "language": "english", "author": {"last_played": 1505959886, "steamid": "76561198030125083", "num_games_owned": 80, "num_reviews": 2, "playtime_forever": 1899, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "votes_funny": 0, "review": "Wow I really loved this game. It was definitely along the